**Question 2 — aircraft per passenger**
The CLI calls the passengers endpoint, then for each passenger it lists the aircraft they have flown on. The passenger data comes back with its aircraft list nested inside.

**Question 3 — airports per aircraft**
The CLI calls the aircraft endpoint and prints each aircraft with the airports it uses.

## Things That Were Tricky

**Paged vs plain responses**
The passengers endpoint returns data wrapped in a "content" object because it is paginated. The aircraft endpoint returns a plain array. I had to write the parsing differently for each so both would map correctly.

**Relationships not saving**
At first the aircraft and passenger links came back empty. The API update methods were not saving the relationship lists, so I added the missing setter calls on the API side and then the links showed up.

**Testing with mocking**
I used JUnit and Mockito to test without a live API. The HTTP client is mocked so I feed it fake JSON and check my code parses it into the right objects.

